cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves using a semantic segmentation branch and a location-agnostic module, which are both related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The self-supervised learning aspect of the location-agnostic module also relates to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the use of a deep detector and inference speed may also relate to robotics (cs.RO).
